词根表
ab- 偏离
ac- 意同 
ad- (缀于 c,k,或 qu 等字母之前)
ad- 加强语气,表增加，变化,方向，靠近
-aholic 沉湎于...的人 
-al …的 
-ance 表示"狀況"的名词词尾 
-anti 表”反”“阻” 
-ard 太过于...的 
-ary 与…有关（的） 
-ate 使(具有…性质)
co-/com-/con-  和...一起;共同
cor 完全（只用于r 前）; 联合
-cy/-acy 具有…职位,具有…性质
de- 离开，去掉
di- 两个，双
en- 使
ex- 不包括，在外
ga 表前进 
-ify/-fy 使得;变成
im 向…内
il/im/ir/in 不，非，无,相反的
infra- 在…以下
-ive/-tive  …性质（的）
-ion/-tion/-ation/-ition/-sion/-xion 表行为或状态
-ish 有…性质的
-ism/’ɪzəm/ 主义；体系
-ist  表示“…的实行者”
litera- 表“文学”
-ory …地方或起;…作用的
-ous 有…特性的
pre- 先于; 在…之前
pro- 往前;支持;亲
re- 重新;在后
-ry/ery  …状态（或性质); …群体（或类）的事物
sub-  在…以下; 次于
sur-  在上,超级,额外的
tri  - 表示"三",
-ture  表行为，过程或结果
-ment  表行为或结果
ne-  不超过…的
re-  重新;再
multi-  多
-ple  …倍

===========
   谓语   | 
===========
B
================
把..看作 treat /triːt/ vt.
【解】treat /triːt/ , consider something in a particular way
【记】eat  treat 请客，招待  以…态度对待  把…看作
【搭】treat …as something 把….看作
【例】它本是伦敦的公司, 但现在却被看作是法国的
It's a London company, but it's now treated as France’s
不要把這件严重的事情當作笑料。
Do not treat this serious matter as a joke.

保持（某种姿势）poise /pɔɪz/ vt.
【解】to be or hold something steady in a particular position, especially above something
 else
【记】pose vi 摆姿势  只摆 1(i)个姿势，就不动了,就是 poise
【例】體操運動員優美地立在平衡木上。
The gymnast poised herself on the balance beam gracefully.
保留 reserve /rɪ’zɜːv/ vt
【解】to keep something for somebody/something, so that it cannot be used by any other
 person or for any other reason
【记】re 再 + serve 提供 vt = 以后再提供出来  保留
【例】给你留了个座位
 These seat is reserved for you.
 我们先把钱存起来，以后用得着
 Let us seserve the money first.We may need it later.
 版权所有
 All Rights Reserved
保证 guarantee [gærən'tiː] vt
【解】Provide a formal assurance or promise, esp. that certain conditions shall be
fulfilled relating to a product, service, or transaction
【记】guard 守卫
【例】我保证完成任务
 I guarantee that the task will be completed.
表扬 commend /kə’mend/ vt
【解】Praise formally or officially
3
【记】表扬（commend）某人是为了让大家共同（com）改善（mend）向典范学习
【例】他因为英勇的行为而被军官表扬了
he was commended by the judge for his courageous actions
praise [preiz] vt
【解】Express warm approval or admiration of
【记】表扬(praise)就是将某人举起(raise vt.)
【例】我们必须好好地表扬一下 Chris，因为他干了件漂亮的活儿
we can't praise Chris enough—he did a brilliant job
波动 fluctuate [ˋflʌktʃʊ͵et] vi
【解】to change frequently in size, amount, quality, etc., especially from one extreme to
 another
【记】波跟流(flow)有关 fl + actuate /'æktʃu’et/ 开动（机器），激励 vt.
fluid 不稳定的，易变的
【例】他大量抛售工业股票，引起了市场波动。
 He undersold a large amount of industrial stocks and caused the
 market to fluctuate.
补充 complement /’kɒmplɪment/ vt
【解】to add to something in a way that improves it or makes it more attractive
【记】补充为了使其变得更完整(complete)
【例】互补
complement each other.
 用这酒配这些菜肴,相得益彰。
 This wine complements the food perfectly.
C

擦亮 polish /’pɒlɪʃ/ vt.
【解】to make something smooth and shiny by rubbing it with a piece of fabric,
often with polish on it
【记】擦亮意味着抛(谐音)光或废除(abolish)污垢
【例】用眼镜布擦攃你的眼镜
 please polish your grasses with the Glasses cloth.
 把我的鞋帮我擦擦
 Please help to polish my shoes
猜想 suppose /sə’pəʊz/ vt.
【解】Assume that something is the case on the basis of evidence or probability
 but without proof or certain knowledge
【记】sup + pose 构成（威胁）
【例】我猜大约 11 点半能到
I suppose I got there about half past eleven
4
拆卸 detach /dɪ’tætʃ/ vt.
【解】to remove something from something larger; to become separated from
 something
【记】de 分离 + 这个零件太次(谐音)了，把它拆下来
【搭】detach …from something 把…从 sth 上拆下来
【例】把内存条从主板上拆下来
 Please detach the memory from the keyboard.
参考 refer /rɪ’fɜː(r)/ vi
【解】to look at something or ask a person for information
【记】ref 有”反回”的含义, ref 反回+ er 表人 反馈给人，供其参考
ref + lect = reflect 反射 vi
ref + use = refuse 拒绝 vi
【搭】refer to something 参考某事
【例】若不能成功登录，请参考下面的 URL 然后联系你本地服务台去获得帮助
If you are experiencing an issue to successfully logging to system, then
please refer to the following URL link and contact your local Help Desk for
assistance.
辞职 resign /rɪ’zaɪn/ vi
【解】to officially tell somebody that you are leaving your job, an organization, etc.
【记】re 重新 + sign 签 = 离职意味着重新和其他公司签约
【辩】retire 退休
【例】我不得不辞职 I have to resign.
测量 measure /’meʒə(r)/ vt
【解】to find the size, quantity, etc. of something in standard units
【记】意味着 mean +肯定 sure
【例】Can you measure it?
沉溺于 abandon oneself to [ə’bændənwʌn,selftə] vt.
【记】放弃(abandon)自己到…中
【例】他沉溺于网络
 He abandon himself to the network.
存在于（某事中）be present [‘prezənt] in
【记】present n. 礼物
 present adj. 在场的
【例】存在于系统中
 be present in the system
乘以 multiply /’mʌltɪplaɪ/ vt.
【记】multi 多 + ply 层
5
【例】五乘以二，乘积是十
 Multiply five by two. The product is ten.
促进 promote /prə’məʊt/ vt.
【解】to help something to happen or develop
【记】pro 向前 + mote 尘埃，微粒 = 向前一点点 促进
【例】首相的访问将促进两国的合作
 The Prime Minister’s visit will promote the cooperation between the two
 countries.
催促 chase /tʃeɪs/ vt
【解】to persuade somebody to do something that they should have done already
【记】chase 还有追的意思
【同】urge
【例】请督促他
Please chase/urge him.
 我一回家，妈就催我写作业
 As soon as I got home My mother always chase/urge me to do homework.
出发 set off
【记】set 使处于某种状态 + off 本身就有“离开”的意思
【例】我们出发之前(状语) before we set off
处理 conduct /kən’dəkt/ vt
【解】Organize and carry out
【记】谁肯(con)处理这件事情
【例】我雇人来处理这件事儿
 I hire agents to conduct this affair.
process /’prəʊses/ vt
【解】to deal officially with a document, request, etc.
【记】process 流程，工序 n.
【辨】process 的处理对象一般是数据,文件等
【例】HK Admin needs 3 working days to process your DOA form
D
打算 intend /ɪn’tend/ vt
【解】to have a plan, result or purpose in your mind when you do something
【记】心里(in)的一种倾向(tend)
【搭】打算做某事
intend to do something
 intend doing something
 打算让某人做某事
 intend somebody to do something
 专为某人（某事）准备的
 Be intended for somebody/something
6
【例】我从未打算呆太久，以免不受欢迎
 I never intend to outstay my welcome
 你们打算什么时候结婚？
 When do you intend to marry?
到位 get sth in place / sth is in place
【解】make sure something located a place it should be on time
【记】get 使（某事）发生 vt.  get sth done
【例】我们必须让所有的包裹在六月前到位
we have to get the everything of the package in place before Jun.
这项培训计划的目的是使你对制裁的风险和控制过程理解到位
This training programme is designed to promote an
understanding of sanctions risks and the control processes
which are in place.
倒扣 invert /ɪn’vɜːt/ vt.
【解】to change the normal position of something by turning it upside down
【记】in 表”相反的” + vertical 垂直的 adj.  仍然是垂直的但是反过来了
【例】她把杯子倒扣在昆蟲上, 將它逮住了。
 She caught the insect by inverting her cup over it.
颠倒 invert /ɪn’vɜːt/ vt.
【解】to change the normal position of something by arranging it in the opposite order
【记】invert 倒扣;颠倒
【例】如果你把"I will"兩字前後轉換一下, 就成為"will I? "
 If you invert "I will" you have "will I? "
 历史数据库中 6 月 18 日和 6 月 27 日的美元对日元的现货汇率被颠倒了
The USD/TRY spot rate for the dates 18 Jun and 27 Jun are inverted in
 the historical database
调查 investigate /ɪn’vestɪɡeɪt/ vt & vi
【解】to carefully examine the facts of a situation, an event, a crime, etc. to find out the
 truth about it or how it happened
【记】调查需要投入(invest)精力
【搭】investigate into something 调查某事
【例】警察正在调查此事
 Policemen is investigating this affair. (as vt.)
 Policemen is investigating into this affair (as vi.)
调出 bring something up
【解】使显示在计算机屏幕上
【记】拿来(bring)显示在屏幕上(up)
【例】请调出 IE 浏览器
 Please bring IE browser up.
 这两条数据记录也被调出来了
 The two records were also brought up.
7
调派 second /sɪ’kɒnd/ vt.
【解】to send an employee to another department, office, etc. in order to do a different
 job for a short period of time
【记】second 是第二的意思，说明 second 表示”临时的”调派
【例】Tony 马上就会被临时调派到香港
Tony is shortly to be seconded to Hong Kong.
登（船，车，飞机）board [bɔ:d] vt
【解】to enter a train, airplane, bus, or ship
【记】登火车意味着踩在木板(board [)上
【例】We will board the plane 30 minutes before it leaves.
蹲 squat /skwɑːt/ vi
【解】to sit on your heels with your knees bent up close to your body
【记】蹲（squat）在广场(square)上
【搭】squat down sth 蹲下
【例】我蹲在他前面
I squatted down in front of him
