发生 arise /ə’raɪz/ vi
【解】especially of a problem or difficult situation to happen.
【例】你们需要应对所有可能发生的问题
You need to tackle all issues that may arise.
occur /ə’kɜː(r)/
【解】to happen
【例】没必要为很久以后发生的事情担心
No need to worry about events that will occur in the distance.
happen /’hæpən/ vi
【解】to take place, especially without being planned.
take place
【解】to happen, especially after previously being arranged or planned
发现 detect /dɪ’tekt/ vt.
【解】to discover or notice something, especially something that is not easy to see, hear,
 etc.
【记】要通过检查 test(tect 形似)才能将目标分离(de)出来，从而发现(de+tect)它
【例】我察觉出她话里有话
 detect other meaning in her words.
发展 advance /əd’vɑːns/ vt.
8
【解】if knowledge, technology, etc.advances, it develops and improves
【记】
【例】发展你的事业
advance your career.
翻转 flip /flɪp/ vi
【解】to turn over into a different position with a sudden quick movement
【记】f(谐音) + lip 嘴唇, 嘴唇似乎是翻着长的
【搭】flip over /flip something … over 翻转
flip through something 草草翻阅
【例】她反到索引，找到了所有的资料
She flipped to the index and found the information she
 needed
反对 oppose /ə’pəʊz/ vt
 【解】to disagree strongly with somebody's plan, policy, etc. and try to change it or
 prevent it from succeeding
【记】反对，就是一种不赞成的姿态(pose)
【同】objection n. 反对
have objection to something = oppose something
【反】approve vt. 赞成
【例】遭到某人强烈反对
be strongly opposed by somebody
 父亲丝毫不反对这个想法
 Father does not oppose the idea at all
仿制 replicate /’replɪkeɪt/ vt.
【解】to copy something exactly
【记】re 再 + pl.复数 + ate 使  使再一次重复，仿制
duplicate /’djuːplɪkeɪt/ vt.
【解】to make an exact copy of something
【记】du 双 + pl.复数 + ate 使  使成双使重复，仿制
放慢 slow down
【例】放慢车速. Slow down your car
 他放慢了步伐 He slow down his step
废除 abolish /ə’bɒlɪʃ/ vt.
【解】to officially end a law, a system or an institution
【记】ab- 偏离 + old 陈旧的 + -ish 有...性质的 = 偏离老一套的事物  废除
【例】南北战争废除了奴隶制
he savery systems was abolished during the Civil War.
abrogate /’æbrəɡeɪt/ vt.
9
【解】to officially end a law, an agreement,
【记】ab- 偏离 + ro (弱 谐音)+ gate 门 = 不再过不好的门了  废除
【例】该法令早在 1970 年就被废除了
This treaty was abrogated as early as1970
分配 assign /ə’saɪn/ vt.
【解】to give somebody something that they can use, or some work or responsibility
【记】as 表原因 + sign 签约 = 因为签约了，所以可以分配
【例】每人分到一間套房
 Each one was assigned a studio.
附加 append /ə’pend/ vt.
【解】to add something to the end of a piece of writing
【记】批准(approve)一般都附加(append)在末尾(end)
【搭】append something to something
 【例】条约上附加了一項新条款
 A new clause was appended to the treaty
G
感冒 have a cold & have a flu
【解】cold /kəʊld/ n, a common illness that affects the nose and/or throat,
making you cough,sneeze, etc.
flu /fluː/ n. an infectious disease like a very bad cold, that causes fever,
pains and weakness
改变 switch /swɪtʃ/ vt.
【解】to change or make something change from one thing to another
【记】switch 开关 n.  使两种状态来回改变
【解】让我们换一个轻松点的话题
 let’s switch the talk to a relaxed subject.
跟…谈谈 have a word with somebody
【解】尤指私下的或祕密的事
【记】与某人有话说
【例】我要私下跟你的谈谈
 I ‘ll have a quiet word with you.。
 上课之前,我想和同学们谈谈昨天的作业情况
 I wanted to have a word with the class about the homework for yesterday before
 the start of class
公布 issue /’ɪʃuː/ vt.
