【记】
【例】对美国国家安全构成威胁
to pose a threat to U.S. national security
核辐射对平民构成持续存在的危险
 Nuclear radiation pose a constant hazard to ordinary populations
compose /kəm’pəʊz/ vt
【解】to combine together to form a whole
【记】com 一起->compose 有组合的味道
【例】英格兰，格兰和威尔士构成了大不列颠岛
 England, Scotland and Wales compose the island of Great Britain.
挂 sling [slɪŋ] vt
【解】Suspend or arrange (something), esp. with a strap or straps, so that it
hangs loosely in a particular position
【记】司令（谐音）挂了 slung 过去式
【搭】to sling sth over sth 将某物挂在某物上
【例】一个吊床被挂在两棵树中间
A hammock was slung between two trees
他把夹克搭在了一个肩膀上
He had his jacket slung over one shoulder
