【记】它it刺（谐音）闹 注：东北方言，刺闹表示痒痒
【例】我皮肤痒痒
 My skin itches.
引发 trigger /’trɪɡə(r)/ vt
【解】to make something happen suddenly
【记】老虎（tiger）引发（trigger）了一场危机
【搭】trigger off = trigger 引起某事
【例】一粒火星引发了这场爆炸
a spark triggered the explosion.
25
 他的行为引发了一场危机
 His action has triggered off a crisis.
应该 ought to /’ɔːt tu/ modal-v & should /ʃʊd/ modal-v
【解】used to say what you advise or recommend
【辨 1】 had better, which is also used to give advise. It’s stronger than should and
ought to. It implies that something bad will happen if the listener does not
follow the advice. It’s often used by someone who has a higher position than
the listener. Had better can be shortened to ‘d better with subject pronouns
【辨 2】 To advise someone not to do something, use should or had better followed
by not and the base form of the main verb. Had better not is stronger than
should not. Ought to is rarely used in the negative form. Should not can be
shortened to shouldn't.
【例】你应该去看医生
You should/ought to go to a doctor.
 你应该多睡会
You should/ought to get more sleep.
